      ],
      "content": "\u003cdiv class\u003d\"introduction\"\u003e\r\n  \u003csection\u003e\r\n    \u003ch4\u003eSafety Stock  Calculated Datase\u003c/h4\u003e\r\n    \u003cdiv class\u003d\"custom-table-container\"\u003e\r\n      \u003cdiv class\u003d\"custom-table-header\"\u003e\r\n        \u003ctable class\u003d\"custom-table\"\u003e\r\n          \u003cthead\u003e\r\n            \u003ctr\u003e\r\n              \u003cth\u003eField Name\u003c/th\u003e\r\n              \u003cth\u003eDescription\u003c/th\u003e\r\n            \u003c/tr\u003e\r\n          \u003c/thead\u003e\r\n        \u003c/table\u003e\r\n      \u003c/div\u003e\r\n\r\n      \u003cdiv class\u003d\"custom-table-body\"\u003e\r\n        \u003ctable class\u003d\"custom-table\"\u003e\r\n          \u003ctbody\u003e\r\n            \u003ctr\u003e\r\n              \u003ctd\u003eIDNRK\u003c/td\u003e\r\n              \u003ctd\u003eUnique identifier for the material (SKU).\u003c/td\u003e\r\n            \u003c/tr\u003e\r\n            \u003ctr\u003e\r\n              \u003ctd\u003eWEEKLY_MEAN_DEMAND\u003c/td\u003e\r\n              \u003ctd\u003eAverage weekly demand based on historical data. Used as Avg Demand in all methods. Converted to daily: Avg Daily \u003d Weekly Mean ÷ 7.\u003c/td\u003e\r\n            \u003c/tr\u003e\r\n            \u003ctr\u003e\r\n              \u003ctd\u003eWEEKLY_STD_DEMAND\u003c/td\u003e\r\n              \u003ctd\u003eStandard deviation of weekly demand (demand variability). Used in Statistical method: σ in Z × σ × √L.\u003c/td\u003e\r\n            \u003c/tr\u003e\r\n            \u003ctr\u003e\r\n              \u003ctd\u003eWEEKLY_MAX_DEMAND\u003c/td\u003e\r\n              \u003ctd\u003ePeak weekly demand observed historically. Used in Max-Avg method: (Max Daily - Avg Daily) × Lead Time.\u003c/td\u003e\r\n            \u003c/tr\u003e\r\n            \u003ctr\u003e\r\n              \u003ctd\u003eMATERIAL_NAME\u003c/td\u003e\r\n              \u003ctd\u003eDescription of the material.\u003c/td\u003e\r\n            \u003c/tr\u003e\r\n            \u003ctr\u003e\r\n              \u003ctd\u003eBASE_UNIT\u003c/td\u003e\r\n              \u003ctd\u003eUnit of measure for inventory (e.g., NOS, KG, M).\u003c/td\u003e\r\n            \u003c/tr\u003e\r\n            \u003ctr\u003e\r\n              \u003ctd\u003eUNIT_PRICE\u003c/td\u003e\r\n              \u003ctd\u003eCost per unit of material. Multiplied by safety stock quantities to compute holding costs (SS_COST_* fields).\u003c/td\u003e\r\n            \u003c/tr\u003e\r\n            \u003ctr\u003e\r\n              \u003ctd\u003eLOT_SIZE\u003c/td\u003e\r\n              \u003ctd\u003eMinimum order quantity (MOQ) or packaging multiple.\u003c/td\u003e\r\n            \u003c/tr\u003e\r\n            \u003ctr\u003e\r\n              \u003ctd\u003eLEAD_TIME_DAYS\u003c/td\u003e\r\n              \u003ctd\u003eSupplier lead time (order-to-delivery duration) in days.\u003c/td\u003e\r\n            \u003c/tr\u003e\r\n            \u003ctr\u003e\r\n              \u003ctd\u003eSS_STATS_95SLA\u003c/td\u003e\r\n              \u003ctd\u003eSafety stock using Statistical method at 95% service level. Calculated as: Z × σ_daily × √L, where Z \u003d 1.64.\u003c/td\u003e\r\n            \u003c/tr\u003e\r\n            \u003ctr\u003e\r\n              \u003ctd\u003eSS_TIME_COVERAGE\u003c/td\u003e\r\n              \u003ctd\u003eSafety stock using Days of Supply method. Calculated as: Avg Daily × Buffer Days (Buffer Days \u003d 7).\u003c/td\u003e\r\n            \u003c/tr\u003e\r\n            \u003ctr\u003e\r\n              \u003ctd\u003eSS_MAX_AVG\u003c/td\u003e\r\n              \u003ctd\u003eSafety stock using Max-Average method. Calculated as: (Max Daily - Avg Daily) × Lead Time.\u003c/td\u003e\r\n            \u003c/tr\u003e\r\n            \u003ctr\u003e\r\n              \u003ctd\u003eSS_COST_95SLA\u003c/td\u003e\r\n              \u003ctd\u003eHolding cost of safety stock using Statistical method at 95% SLA. Calculated as: SS_STATS_95SLA × UNIT_PRICE.\u003c/td\u003e\r\n            \u003c/tr\u003e\r\n            \u003ctr\u003e\r\n              \u003ctd\u003eSS_COST_TIMECOVG\u003c/td\u003e\r\n              \u003ctd\u003eHolding cost of safety stock using Days of Supply method. Calculated as: SS_TIME_COVERAGE × UNIT_PRICE.\u003c/td\u003e\r\n            \u003c/tr\u003e\r\n            \u003ctr\u003e\r\n              \u003ctd\u003eSS_COST_MAXAVG\u003c/td\u003e\r\n              \u003ctd\u003eHolding cost of safety stock using Max-Average method. Calculated as: SS_MAX_AVG × UNIT_PRICE.\u003c/td\u003e\r\n            \u003c/tr\u003e\r\n          \u003c/tbody\u003e\r\n        \u003c/table\u003e\r\n      \u003c/div\u003e\r\n    \u003c/div\u003e\r\n  \u003c/section\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n",
